senses
  entry
    definition "a way of regarding situations or topics etc."
    examples ("consider what follows from the positivist view")
    id oewn-06218486-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (position perspective)
  entry
    definition "the visual percept of a region"
    examples ("the most desirable feature of the park are the beautiful views")
    id oewn-05941982-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (aspect prospect scene vista panorama)
  entry
    definition "the act of looking or seeing or observing"
    examples ("he tried to get a better view of it" "his survey of the battlefield was limited")
    id oewn-00883327-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (survey sight)
  entry
    definition "the range of the eye"
    examples ("they were soon out of view")
    id oewn-08578489-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (eyeshot)
  entry
    definition "a personal belief or judgment that is not founded on proof or certainty"
    examples ("my opinion differs from yours" "I am not of your persuasion" "what are your thoughts on Haiti?")
    id oewn-05954491-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (opinion sentiment persuasion thought)
  entry
    definition "a message expressing a belief about something; the expression of a belief that is held with confidence but not substantiated by positive knowledge or proof"
    examples ("his opinions appeared frequently on the editorial page")
    id oewn-06794876-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (opinion)
  entry
    definition "purpose; the phrase ‘with a view to’ means ‘with the intention of’ or ‘for the purpose of’"
    examples ("he took the computer with a view to pawning it")
    id oewn-05992348-n
    partOfSpeech n
  entry
    definition "graphic art consisting of the graphic or photographic representation of a visual percept"
    examples ("he painted scenes from everyday life" "figure 2 shows photographic and schematic views of the equipment")
    id oewn-04151847-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (scene)
  entry
    definition "the range of interest or activity that can be anticipated"
    examples ("It is beyond the horizon of present knowledge")
    id oewn-05135047-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (horizon purview)
  entry
    definition "outward appearance"
    examples ("they look the same in outward view")
    id oewn-04682218-n
    partOfSpeech n
  entry
    definition "deem to be"
    examples ("She views this quite differently from me" "I consider her to be shallow" "I don't see the situation quite as negatively as you do")
    id oewn-00692380-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms (see consider reckon regard)
  entry
    definition "look at carefully; study mentally"
    examples ("view a problem")
    id oewn-02134765-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms (consider "look at")
  entry
    definition "see or watch"
    examples ("view a show on television" "This program will be seen all over the world" "view an exhibition" "Catch a show on Broadway" "see a movie")
    id oewn-02155378-v
